This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks that require knowledge about the world, specifically reasoning over knowledge graphs (KGs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and vector representations, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with knowledge base completion and path query answering, which are related to databases and information retrieval, respectively, making cs.DB and cs.IR likely sub-categories as well.
